        <section class="section-content section-gratuity" id="section-gratuity">
          <h3 class="section-title">
            Gratuity for you or Your family
            <small>...applicable if Employee is appointed on or before 31st December 2003</small>
          </h3>
          <p><strong>Gratuity</strong> is a Lumpsum amount payable on Retirement (to the Employee) or in the event of death of Employee in service (to his/her Family).</p>
          <p> Gratuity amount is based on <strong> Length of Qualifying Service </strong> and the <strong> Last Pay drawn</strong> by the Employee.</p>
          <p>If Employee has NOT put in TEN years of Qualifying service at the time of Retirement , he will NOT get Pension. Instead he will get <strong> SERVICE GRATUITY </strong></p>
          <p><strong>Calculation Formula for Service Gratuity : Number of every completed six-monthly period of service X Half-month's Emoluments</strong></p>
          <p><li> Service Gratuity is in ADDITION to Retirement Gratuity (if payable- as explained below).</li></p>
          <p><strong>RETIREMENT GRATUITY</strong> is paid to
          <p><li> A <strong> Permanent </strong> Employee who has put in FIVE years or more years of Qualifying service at the time of Retirement </li></p>
          <p><li>A <strong> Temporary </strong> Employee who has put in TEN years or more years of Qualifying service at the time of retiring on attaining the age of superannuation or on invalidation. </li></p>
          <p><strong> IMPORTANT : </strong> Retirement Gratuity may <strong> Lapse </strong> in the event of death of employee - AFTER retirement BUT before receiving the Gratuity<p>
          <li> If he leaves behind NO family ,or
          <li> If no Nomination has been made .or
          <li> If Nomination done BUT Nominee does not subsist</li>
          In above cases Retirement Gratuity will be paid to THE person who produces a SUCCESSION CERTIFICATE from a Court of Law , else Retirement Gratuity will lapse.</p>

          <div class="col-md-9 col-sm-9 col-lg-9">
            <div class="panel-heading">
              <h4 class="panel-title">
                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1">
                  <p> To whom the Leave Encashment is payable in case of death of Employee ?</p>
                </a>
              </h4>
            </div>
