              <div class="panel-body">
                <p>In the event of death of Employee AFTER retirement or final cessation of duty BUT before actual receipt of Cash Equivalent of Leave Salary , the amount will be paid to any of his Family in following order.</p>
                <li> To the Widow / Husband as the case may be.</li>
                <li> To the Eldest Surving Widow - if there are more than one widow . Seniority will be decided with respect to date of marriage and not with reference to their age.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving Son or an adopted son.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving unmarried daughter.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving widowed daughter.</li>
                <li> else To the Father.</li>
                <li> else To the Mother.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving Brother below the age of 18 years.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving nmarried Sister.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving widowed Sister.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Surviving married Daughter.</li>
                <li> else To the Eldest Child of the eldest pre-deceased son.</li></p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>






          <p> Employee is entitle to get <strong> INTEREST ON DELAYED PAYMENTS </strong> of Gratuity amount if the delay is beyond 3 months due to any administrative lapse. Interest rate will be GPF Interest rate compounded annually.</p>
          <p> If payment of Gratuity is <strong> WITHHELD</strong> due to any pending departmental / judiciary proceedings and Employee is exonerated on conclusion of proceedings , Interest on due Gratuity amount will stand payable at GPF interest rate compounded annually.</p>
          <p><li>Retirement Gratuity is NOT Taxable under Income Tax Rules.</li>
          <li>Retirement Gratuity amount is NOT liable to Court attachment under the provisions of Code of Civil Procedures.</li>
          <li>Govt.dues if any , at the time of retirement MAY be RECOVERED WITHOUT EMPLOYEE's CONSENT from gratuity amount.</li></p>


