        <section class="section-content section-EL" id="section-EL">
          <h3 class="section-title">
            Encashment of Earn Leaves & HPL
            <small>for the leaves in balance as on last day of service</small>
          </h3>
          <p>One time Lumpsum payment of Cash equivalent of Leave Salary admissible for the days of EARNED leaves and Half-Pay Leaves - put together on the last day of service , subject to a maximum of 300 days.</p>
          <p><strong> Leave Encashment is granted when</strong>
          <p><li> Employee retires from service on attaining the age of superannuation.</li>
          <li> Employee gets an extension of service - beyond superannuation in public interest</li>
          <li> Employee under suspension or disciplinary or criminal proceeding pending on the date of superannuation - if Authority has a view that there is no probability of any amount recoverable on conclusion of proceedings.</li>
          <li> Employee is Invalidated from services on Medical grounds.</li>
          <li> Employee takes Premature Retirement under the provisions of Financial Rules ( 56 j or l ) or CCS (Pension) rules (48).</li>
          <li> Employee takes Voluntary Retirement under the provisions of Financial Rules ( 56 k or m ) or CCS (Pension) rules (48 / 48 A).</li>
          <li> Employee resigns on his own accord.Cash equivalent will be only to the extent of half of the earned leave at credit subject to a maximum of 150 days.</li>
          <li> Employee is retired Compulsury as a measure of penalty evn if reduction of pension is ordered.</li>
          <li> Termination of service by giving notice or by paying pay & allowances in lieu of notice or in accordance with the terms & conditions of employment.</li>
          <li> Termination of service on Re-employment. The period for which Leave Encashment was allowed by previous employer will be CLUBBED with overall ceiling of 300 days of Leave Encashment allowed on date of retirement.</li>
          <p><strong>Calculation Formula for Leave Encashment : </strong></p>
          <p><strong> IMPORTANT : </strong></p>
          <li> Pay + Personal Pay + Dearness Allowance as admissible on the last day of service is taken into account for calculation purposes. Personal Pay for promoting small family norms and Personal Pay for passing of Hindi Examination are EXCLUDED for the said purposes.</li>
          <li> Any increase in DA rates with retrospective effect will be taken into calculation and payment of arrears to Employee.</li>
          <li> EL Encashment taken on availing LTC is NOT taken into consideration while putting ceiling of maximum 300 days of EL encashment.</li>
          <li> Cash Equivalent of leave salary - up to TEN months is NOT liable to Income Tax.</li>

        </section>

