        <section class="section-content section-pensionapply" id="section-pensionapply">
          <h3 class="section-title">
            When Pension may be applied ?
            <small>there are Four Situations when Pension may be applied for</small>
          </h3>
          <p>There are Four Pensions -  <strong>Superannuation , Early Pension , Family Pension & Disability Pension</strong> which may be availed by a Member and his/her Family.</p>
                                                            <pre>
                            1- On Superannuation i.e. on attaining age of 58 years PROVIDED at least 10 years of service has been completed.
                            On attaining 58 Years of age, EPF member ceases to be a member of EPS automatically.
                            The member can CONTINUE in service while receiving Superannuation pension.</p>
                                                              2- Before Superannuation i.e. on attaining age of 50 years PROVIDED at least 10 years of service has been completed and member has NOT attained age of 58 years.
                            The member opting Early Pension should not be in service.</p>
                                                              3- On Death of a member whether Member is in service or NOT in service - Nominated Family person will get Pension i.e. Family Pension.</p>
                                                              4- On Permanent disability i.e. when a member is Permanently and totally unfit for the employment which the member was doing at the time of such disablement.</pre>
          <p>•    No pensioner can receive more than one EPF Pension.</p>
        </section>

